fields.job_description:
1. Partner closely with HRBPs and Hiring Managers to ensure sourcing and hiring strategies are aligned with TikTok people strategies.
2. Partner with business leaders and hiring managers to assess their talent requirements and fulfill hiring plans along with business timelines.
3. Use your established networks to discover, and attract experienced, diverse, ambitious talent to join our team.
4. Screen and select candidates effectively by assessing both their previous experience as well as culture fit with TikTok environment.
5. Lead key initiatives and projects with the Trust & Safety team, and other recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results.
6. Provide an efficient and high-touch experience for every candidate from the application stage to offer, evaluating skill level, driving the interview process and offer process, including reference checks, salary recommendations and closing of candidates.
fields.job_requirements:
1. Strong communication and organisational skills.
2. Keen attention to detail, and experience in both building and executing recruiting processes.
3. Passionate about providing a great experience for all our candidates, whether they pass or not.
4. Entrepreneurial and creative problem-solving ability - you'll have lots of support but often have to figure out the solution yourself.
5. Experience closing senior and/or executive-level candidates and negotiating complex compensation packages.
6. Optimistic and collaborative - we're building an awesome team and looking for someone excited to roll their sleeves up and join us as we start this journey.

fields.job_description:
1. Enhance the people and workplace experience through localized people initiatives throughout the employee lifecycle, including process improvements, data & insights.
2. Provide support and knowledge to the business for the whole employee lifecycle. Continually, work on the enhancement of the employee lifecycle through process improvements, automation, data & insights.
3. Help scale various HR programs to create efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies, and programs.
4. Maintain partnerships with geographically distributed HRBPs, TA and other HR Operations team members.
5. Exercise independent judgment and discretion do determine appropriate actions or solutions to problems.
fields.job_requirements:
1. Bachelor's degree or above.
2. 6+ years of People Operations/Human Resources related experience.
3. Support employees and improve employee experience by providing end to end HR solution to solve their issues.
4. Actively educate employees and managers on how to stay within legal guidelines regarding on-the-job behaviour, investigate workplace violations, and respond to stakeholder queries though a combination of referring to internal experts, and/or interpreting both policies and changes to policy.
5. Strong business partnering skills and HR acumen, including problem solving skills, critical thinking abilities, coaching skills, project management & leadership abilities.
6. Analytical and problem-solving skills.
7. Player-coach role, with the experience of managing a small team.
8. High level of discretion, confidentiality, and ethics.
9. Humility, flexibility, good interpersonal & customer facing skills are a must.
10. Highly proficient and excellent communication skills in English.

fields.job_description:
1. Partner closely with HRBPs and Hiring Managers to ensure sourcing and hiring strategies are aligned with TikTok people strategies.
2. Partner with business leaders and hiring managers to assess their talent requirements and fulfill hiring plans along with business timelines.
3. Use your established networks to discover, and attract experienced, diverse, ambitious talent to join our team.
4. Screen and select candidates effectively by assessing both their previous experience as well as culture fit with TikTok environment.
5. Lead key initiatives and projects with the Trust & Safety team, and other recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results.
6. Provide an efficient and high-touch experience for every candidate from the application stage to offer, evaluating skill level, driving the interview process and offer process, including reference checks, salary recommendations and closing of candidates.
fields.job_requirements:
1. Strong communication and organisational skills.
2. Keen attention to detail, and experience in both building and executing recruiting processes.
3. Passionate about providing a great experience for all our candidates, whether they pass or not.
4. Entrepreneurial and creative problem-solving ability - you'll have lots of support but often have to figure out the solution yourself.
5. Experience closing senior and/or executive-level candidates and negotiating complex compensation packages.
6. Optimistic and collaborative - we're building an awesome team and looking for someone excited to roll their sleeves up and join us as we start this journey.

fields.job_description:
1. Enhance the people and workplace experience through localized people initiatives throughout the employee lifecycle, including process improvements, data & insights.
2. Provide support and knowledge to the business for the whole employee lifecycle. Continually, work on the enhancement of the employee lifecycle through process improvements, automation, data & insights.
3. Help scale various HR programs to create efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies, and programs.
4. Maintain partnerships with geographically distributed HRBPs, TA and other HR Operations team members.
5. Exercise independent judgment and discretion do determine appropriate actions or solutions to problems.
fields.job_requirements:
1. Bachelor's degree or above.
2. 6+ years of People Operations/Human Resources related experience.
3. Support employees and improve employee experience by providing end to end HR solution to solve their issues.
4. Actively educate employees and managers on how to stay within legal guidelines regarding on-the-job behaviour, investigate workplace violations, and respond to stakeholder queries though a combination of referring to internal experts, and/or interpreting both policies and changes to policy.
5. Strong business partnering skills and HR acumen, including problem solving skills, critical thinking abilities, coaching skills, project management & leadership abilities.
6. Analytical and problem-solving skills.
7. Player-coach role, with the experience of managing a small team.
8. High level of discretion, confidentiality, and ethics.
9. Humility, flexibility, good interpersonal & customer facing skills are a must.
10. Highly proficient and excellent communication skills in English.

fields.name: Norsyuhada Fairos
fields.title: iOS Developer
fields.description:
Exceptionally creative and dependable entry level developer with a very good work ethic 
and broadly knowledgeable in a wide variety of technologies as well as the principles and 
techniques of website and mobile application development, testing and maintenance. 
 
PROJECTS: 
CryptoCalcy | iOS App 
CryptoCalcy lets users view prices and comparisons between regular fiat money with 
cryptocurrencies allowing them to keep track of their favorite cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, 
Ethereum, Ripple and many more. This app uses an API from CryptoCompare to get prices 
for various currencies. 
 
Feedetite | iOS App 
Feedetite is an RSS aggregator iOS app that can be used to read RSS, ATOM and JSON feeds. 
It gets latest news from major news media outlets like CNN, BBC, The Atlantic and many 
others. Users can follow a feed or add their own source by entering a feed URL from a 
source. Users can also collect articles in separate journals for future reference. 
 
SeaFood | iOS App 
SeaFood is an iOS App that uses Apple's CoreML framework and Google's InceptionV3 
machine learning model to detect and recognize images of objects or scenes taken by the 
iPhone's camera by the User. 
 
Clima | iOS App 
Clima is a weather app that shows weather information about a particular city using the 
OpenWeatherMap API. Users can view weather information for a default city or they can 
see weather information for any other place by entering the city's name. 
 
Todoey | iOS App 
Todoey is a simple minimalistic to-do list app. Users can add new events to a list and also 
has the ability to create new categories of lists based on their preferences. 
 
Weight Tracker | React App 
Weight Tracker is a web app that uses React.js on the front-end and Firebase on the 
backend. A User can login through their existing account or they can create new account. 
Every time a user enters their weight, it gets stored in the database i.e. on Firebase. The app 
pulls those data and plots a graph of their weight with respect to the time of their entry. 
 
Calculator | React App 
This is a simple calculator web app also based on React. The UI is inspired from iOS 
Calculator app. It performs basic arithmetic operations.

fields.title: IT Audit Manager
fields.description: Job Role: Internal Audit reports to the Audit Committee of the Board of Directors. Internal Audit's primary mission is to provide assurance to the Board of Directors and Executive Management that Accenture's businesses are well managed and meeting strategic, operational and risk management objectives. The team engages with senior leaders and all of Accenture's individual business units globally to understand and advise on the risks in their business, evaluate the effectiveness of key processes and assist in the design of best practices that can improve their results. Internal Audit's work builds confidence that Accenture will meet its obligations to clients, shareholders, employees and other stakeholders. Key responsibilities include: Conducting IT application and infrastructure security, ventures & acquisitions, regulatory and risk advisory audits and assessment across APAC and Europe regions (all on-site) Conduct annual IT risk assessment process to draft the annual IT audit plan. Manage end-to-end audit lifecycle by leading the audits: - Audit Pre-planning - Presentation of audit deck to Chief Audit Executive (CAE) - Audit fieldwork (Testing - Test of Design and Test of Operating Effectiveness) - Audit Reporting (Reporting) - Audit Issue Tracking to Closure Helped setting up a new IT Internal Audit team in Ireland, Dublin w.r.t hiring, training and on-boarding. Reviewing teams work to ensure quality of audit deliverables including pre-planning and planning decks, audit reports and workpapers. Finalizing the quarterly audit schedule, scheduling and leading audit scoping calls, resource plotting and budget finalization. Internal Audit departmental initiatives to streamline processes and skills enhancements to stay ahead and stay relevant in today's ever-changing business landscape. Participate in regular meetings with key business stakeholders to understand the IT risk landscape in their domain and assess the engagements for a potential audit. Developing the complete audit approach, scope, and providing an update to the Chief Audit Executive during the audit planning meeting and obtaining sign off. Lead the planning and execution of APAC and Middle East audits to ensure all IT audit engagements are well planned, timely executed within the budgeted time and expenses. Conducting IT security audits of projects delivering IT services to clients across different industry segments viz. Aviation, Banking, Manufacturing, Energy, Pharmaceuticals, Telecom etc. Lead the APAC and ME IT Acquisitions, Joint Ventures, Accenture's internal technology (CIO e.g. Wireless, DLP, Internet Filtering, O365, RPA, IoT Implementations etc.) and client service delivery audits. Support Integrated audits and supporting the finance audit teams in the geography reviews for IT. Performing annual/ongoing risk assessment process and to evaluate IT risk across the APAC region and the technology risk. Track follow-up and reporting of open audit findings with the remediation action plans for APAC IT audits to the Audit Committee. Define the risk and control matrix along with the audit test procedures for the key IT control testing to ensure the effectiveness and efficiency of audit assignments. Provide formal weekly audit status updates to the Internal Audit Senior management team.

fields.title: Sr. Big Data Consultant
fields.description: Description: Pentaho is a company that provides data integration with ETL capabilities, data mining, OLAP services, reporting, and dashboading. Pentaho was founded in 2004 by five founders and is headquartered in Orlando, FL, USA. Pentaho Data Integration, codenamed Kettle, consists of a core data integration (ETL) engine, and GUI applications that allow the user to define data integration jobs and transformations. It supports deployment on single node computers as well as on cloud, or cluster. Pentaho for Big Data is a data integration tool based on Pentaho Data Integration. fields.title: J2EE Consultant
fields.description: Description: Production & Store systems support (Analysis, problem determination and trouble shooting of applications, Integration of enhancements, Applying upgrades and patches, Automation of daily routine tasks) for Apollo Pharmacy (AP) systems. Responsibilities: End to End designing of Critical Core Java Components using Java Collections and Multithreading. Analysis of different database schemas Transaction and Data warehouse to build extensive reports to Business using SQL & Joins. Development of multiple reports to business in quick turn-around time, which helped business to save considerable operational costs. Created one of the best programs to notify the operational team on Downtime of one of 250 pharmacies on AP network in a few seconds. Created an interface using JSP, Servlet and MVC Struts architecture for pharmacy team to resolve stuck orders in different pharmacies. Performance tuned the IMS report to memory leaks and best practices in java to boost the performance and reliability of the application. Environment: Java 1.4, J2EE (JSP, Servlets, Java Beans, JDBC, Multi-Threading), LINUX (Shell & Perl Scripting), and SQL.
